snippet.textDisplay: As a pleasantly plump woman and someone that has fluctuated between sick skinny and being obese, I get it. I have a lot of empathy for Shane. As long as he is happy and healthy, that's what matters. It's the internet. Everyone is up for criticism. However, I don't think that should include shots at people's appearances. If you have to comment low blows like that, you're just being mean and completely unproductive. I have certain opinions and criticism of some of his motives like with the makeup series/products, but that is based on his actions. Not his looks. I really don't even think he looks that bad. And he seems to be very self-aware of his own issues. I wish him well.
